data_totaltime = np.array([
    [10000,0.0001 ],
    [100000,0.00046 ],
    #[1000000, 0.00038],
    [1000000,0.00305],
    [10000000,0.0029 ],
    [100000000,0.02967 ],
    #[1000000000,0.05085 ],
    [1000000000,0.28348],
    [10000000000,0.53645 ],
    [100000000000,5.23731 ],
    #[100000000000,12.90995 ],
    [1000000000000, 138.59632]
])

data_matchtime = np.array([
    [10000,0.00003],
    [100000,0.0002],
    [1000000,0.00194],
    #[1000000, 0.00019],
    [10000000,0.00177],
    [100000000,0.01949],
    #[1000000000,0.04122],
    [1000000000,0.19065],
    [10000000000,0.44433],
    [100000000000, 4.33195],
    #[100000000000,12.81745],
    [1000000000000, 137.68859]
])
    
x, y = data_totaltime.T

plt.figure(figsize=(25,12))
plt.loglog(x,y, marker="o", label="Total Time")
    
x, y = data_matchtime.T
plt.loglog(x,y, marker="*",label="Match Time")

plt.grid()
plt.xlabel("Slen x Plen", fontsize = 18)

plt.ylabel("Total Time [s]", fontsize = 18)

plt.legend( fontsize=20)
plt.title("Serial Version 1",  fontsize=18)

plt.show()
plt.savefig('Serial.png')

# Total times 4 cores
# Version 1 break 
# Version 1 task 
# Seriale 1

#Misurazioni: per S 10^5 P 10^3 - S 10^6 P 10^3 - S 10^7 P 10^3 - S 10^7 P 10^4


serial = np.array([
    [100000000, 0.00581 ],
    [1000000000,0.05085 ],
    [10000000000,0.53645 ],
    [100000000000,12.90995 ],
    [1000000000000, 138.59632]
])

serial2 = np.array([
    [100000000, 0.00443 ],
    [1000000000, 0.04578 ],
    [10000000000, 0.44850],
    [100000000000,13.19 ], #
    [1000000000000,145.08619 ] #
])

v1= np.array([
    [100000000,0.00515],
    [1000000000,0.04642],
    [10000000000,0.46656],
    [100000000000,10.24702],
    [1000000000000, 102.76884]
])

v2= np.array([
    [100000000, 0.00603  ],
    [1000000000, 0.06019],
    [10000000000, 0.53143] ,
    [100000000000, 8.08145], 
    [1000000000000, 78.75924]
])


x, y = serial.T
plt.figure(figsize=(13,10))
plt.semilogx(x,y, marker="o",  label="Serial V1")

x, y = serial2.T
plt.semilogx(x,y, marker="o",  label="Serial V2")

x, y = v1.T
plt.semilogx(x,y, marker="*",  label="Parallel V1")

x, y = v2.T
plt.semilogx(x,y, marker="+",  label="Parallel V2")

plt.grid()
plt.xlabel("Slen x Plen", fontsize = 18)
plt.ylabel("Total Time [s]", fontsize = 18)
plt.title("Serial vs Parallel 2 cores V1 and V2", fontsize = 18)
plt.legend(loc="upper left", fontsize = 20)
plt.show()
